ornia Historical Society","start_year":1922,"notes":"Reactivated the Society in 1922 after it had lapsed; made honorary member for life."},{"role":"Active Board Member","organization":"Save the Redwoods League / California Academy of Sciences / Friends of the Bancroft Library"}],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[{"landmark_id":"LM123"}],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"tags":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[{"type":"parallel_careers","related_id":"HD6074","display_label":"also a pioneering historian of Gold Rush California"}],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"civic","header":"Grand old man of Stiles Hall, fifty years","body":"Anson Stiles Blake chaired the board of the University YMCA at UC Berkeley for fifty years — the building, Stiles Hall, took its name from a benefactor in his Stiles family line. The California State Legislature formally named him the 'Grand old man of Stiles Hall' in recognition of that service."},{"number":2,"category":"civic","header":"Reactivated the California Historical Society, 1922","body":"When the California Historical Society had lapsed, Anson Stiles Blake organized its 1922 revival and served as president. The Society later made him an honorary member for life. He sat on the boards of the Save the Redwoods League, California Academy of Sciences, and Friends of the Bancroft Library."},{"number":3,"category":"career","header":"Family quarry firm at Richmond, California","body":"Anson presided over Blake Brothers Co., the family quarry business at Richmond, California — extending into industrial materials a Blake-family talent for working stone that had begun with his grandfather Eli Whitney Blake's invention of the stone crusher in the 1850s."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"label":"FindAGrave memorial 137272119","url":"https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/137272119/anson_stiles-blake"}],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"anson-blake-1870"}},"burialCemetery":{"id":"CEM310","name":"Sunse